## Why This Is Asked

Tests knowledge of how CPU frequency scaling and turbo decisions influence latency. It also assesses ability to use default tools for correlation, triage threads, and apply targeted mitigations without disturbing others.

## Key Concepts

- CPU frequency scaling and turbo boost
- Per-core scheduling and affinity
- Observability: perf, tracepoints, kernel logs

## Code Example

```javascript
// diag.js
const {execSync} = require('child_process');
try {
  const g = execSync("grep -h 'scaling_governor' /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor", {stdio:['ignore','pipe','ignore']}).toString().trim();
  console.log("Governors:\n" + g);
} catch {
  console.log("Governors unavailable");
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you adapt this workflow for NUMA or SMT?
- What changes if you cannot modify the governor on all CPUs?

